com.microsoft.azure.management.network

Interface LoadBalancer.UpdateStages.WithPublicIpAddress

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    LoadBalancer.Update, LoadBalancer.UpdateStages.WithInternetFrontend
    Enclosing interface:
    LoadBalancer.UpdateStages

    public static interface LoadBalancer.UpdateStages.WithPublicIpAddress
    The stage of a load balancer update allowing to add a public IP address as the default public frontend.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      LoadBalancer.Update withExistingPublicIpAddress(PublicIpAddress publicIpAddress)
      Assigns the provided public IP address to the default public frontend to the load balancer.
      LoadBalancer.Update withNewPublicIpAddress()
      Creates a new public IP address as the default public frontend of the load balancer, using an automatically generated name and leaf DNS label derived from the load balancer's name, in the same resource group and region.
      LoadBalancer.Update withNewPublicIpAddress(Creatable<PublicIpAddress> creatablePublicIpAddress)
      Adds a new public IP address to the default front end of the load balancer.
      LoadBalancer.Update withNewPublicIpAddress(String dnsLeafLabel)
      Adds a new public IP address as the default public frontend of the load balancer, using the specified DNS leaf label, an automatically generated frontend name derived from the DNS label, in the same resource group and region as the load balancer.

    • Method Detail

      • withExistingPublicIpAddress

        LoadBalancer.Update withExistingPublicIpAddress(PublicIpAddress publicIpAddress)
        Assigns the provided public IP address to the default public frontend to the load balancer.

        This will create a new default frontend for the load balancer under the name "default", if one does not already exist.

        Parameters:
        publicIpAddress - an existing public IP address
        Returns:
        the next stage of the update

      • withNewPublicIpAddress

        LoadBalancer.Update withNewPublicIpAddress()
        Creates a new public IP address as the default public frontend of the load balancer, using an automatically generated name and leaf DNS label derived from the load balancer's name, in the same resource group and region.

        This will create a new default frontend for the load balancer under the name "default", if one does not already exist.

        Returns:
        the next stage of the update

      • withNewPublicIpAddress

        LoadBalancer.Update withNewPublicIpAddress(String dnsLeafLabel)
        Adds a new public IP address as the default public frontend of the load balancer, using the specified DNS leaf label, an automatically generated frontend name derived from the DNS label, in the same resource group and region as the load balancer.
        Parameters:
        dnsLeafLabel - a DNS leaf label
        Returns:
        the next stage of the update

      • withNewPublicIpAddress

        LoadBalancer.Update withNewPublicIpAddress(Creatable<PublicIpAddress> creatablePublicIpAddress)
        Adds a new public IP address to the default front end of the load balancer.
        Parameters:
        creatablePublicIpAddress - the creatable stage of a public IP address definition
        Returns:
        the next stage of the update
